'''Rutgers WPF''' is a [[The Netherlands|Dutch]] expert centre on [[human sexual behavior|sexuality]], based in [[Utrecht (city)|Utrecht]].

Rutgers WPFp was established in 1999 as the result of a fusion between Rutgers Stichting (1969) and Nisso (1967). Rutgers WPF consists of two departments: Research and Development, and Implementation. They also have a Youth Sex Offender project and a Youth Incentives programme to promote sexual health. It is the [[International Planned Parenthood Federation]]'s affiliate in the Netherlands.

Ministries, municipalities, care institutions, educational institutes, pressure groups, but also companies make use of their expertise.

